      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the screw-rod assembly. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for peak von Mises stress at screw-rod interface: 1.8%. Final mesh (1.2 M elements, average element size 0.15 mm at critical regions) selected as production mesh."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals monitored; force and moment equilibrium checked at each load step. Required Gradation 2: residuals reported and within tolerance.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson nonlinear solver converged to force residual <0.01% and displacement residual <0.005% at all 20 load steps. Energy balance error <0.1% for all 11 virtual constructs. No spurious hourglass energy detected."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation workflow with independent peer review of boundary conditions and loading. Required Gradation 2: independent review completed and documented.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup (boundary conditions, contact definitions, material assignments) independently reviewed by a second FDA engineer not involved in model development. Review checklist completed and signed. Two minor discrepancies in contact stiffness settings identified and corrected prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with nonlinear geometry and bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity for Ti-6Al-4V. Required Gradation 3: physics-appropriate constitutive model with documented justification.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) plasticity applied to Ti-6Al-4V screw and rod components. Geometric nonlinearity (NLGEOM ON) activated to capture large-displacement response at 40 mm endpoint. UHMWPE vertebral body surrogate modeled as linear elastic — consistent with ASTM F1717 test block material behavior at test rates."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties derived from coupon testing of production-lot Ti-6Al-4V; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of test specimens. Required Gradation 3: inputs traceable to specimen-specific measurements.",
      "rationale": "Young's modulus (113.8 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus (2.2 GPa) derived from tensile coupon tests on production-lot bar stock (n=5 coupons, ASTM E8). Screw and rod geometry inputs from CMM measurements of five representative specimens; nominal dimensions used for remaining constructs with documented dimensional tolerance sensitivity study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories; specimens from production lots. Required Gradation 3: multi-lab testing with production-representative specimens.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production inventory tested: six at FDA CDRH biomechanics laboratory and five at DePuy Synthes R&D. All specimens traceable to production lot certificates of conformance. Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness: 3.2%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions should span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two displacement rates or load configurations to achieve Gradation 3. Required Gradation 3: multiple test conditions bracketing COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "All testing performed at a single crosshead displacement rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 protocol. No variation in loading rate, temperature, or construct angulation was explored. This limits the test condition coverage to a single nominal condition and precludes assessment of rate sensitivity or configuration sensitivity relevant to the clinical COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry and displacement-controlled ramp. Required Gradation 3: documented equivalency mapping between test and model inputs.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 fixture geometry digitized from laboratory drawings and replicated in FEA assembly. Displacement-controlled ramp at 5 mm/min applied as prescribed displacement boundary condition. Fixture compliance measured experimentally and incorporated as spring elements in the model. Equivalency mapping table documented in FDA technical report TR-2023-007."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using validation metric E/uval with acceptance threshold <1.96 (95% confidence interval) and percent difference <10% for all three QoIs. Required Gradation 3: statistical validation metric with pre-specified acceptance criteria.",
      "rationale": "Pre-specified acceptance criteria: E/uval < 1.96 and |% difference| < 10% for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm. Results: stiffness E/uval = 1.21 (7.3% diff), yield force E/uval = 0.94 (4.1% diff), force at 40 mm E/uval = 1.08 (5.6% diff). All three QoIs pass both criteria. Validation metric computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly map to ASTM F1717 acceptance endpoints and clinical performance indicators. Required Gradation 3: QoIs directly linked to COU decision criteria.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing between implant and spine segment. Yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation relevant to fatigue life. Force at 40 mm is the ASTM F1717 standard endpoint used in regulatory submissions. All three QoIs are explicitly referenced in the COU decision criteria and the 510(k) predicate comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717 bench test) matches the intended COU (predict static compression-bending performance for regulatory submission). Required Gradation 3: direct correspondence between validation scenario and COU.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity replicates the exact regulatory test (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending) that the FEA model is intended to support. Same construct geometry, same loading protocol, same performance endpoints. No extrapolation beyond the validated scenario is claimed in the regulatory submission."
