    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achievedLevel 2 vs. requiredLevel 3) is considered acceptable given that the ASTM F1717 protocol is prescriptive and single-condition testing is standard regulatory practice. The overall credibility profile supports a Medium assurance level consistent with modelRiskLevel 3 and the Medium decision consequence and model influence ratings. The assessment team concludes that the FEA model provides adequate credibility for the intended regulatory submission.",
